Genetic Algorithms, Probabilistic Methods. 

Genetic Algorithms: The paper describes an algorithm based on a traditional genetic algorithm (GA) and how it is used to efficiently locate all optima of multimodal problems. 

Probabilistic Methods: The paper uses a fitness derating function to depress fitness values in the regions of the problem space where solutions have already been found. This increases the likelihood of discovering a new solution on each iteration, which is a probabilistic approach.
